        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Dunno what to make of all that. I assist heal constantly, whenever im in a group, a raid. whatever. Our heal is 10 mana, and we're sucking life outta stuff anyway, so why not? I've always viewed backup mezzing as my JOB in an xp group. During pulls of 3 or more mobs SOMEONE is gonna end up getting smacked around by an unslowed mob, so hell, mez it and let the chanter overwrite. np. ST seems to pull a TON of aggro, moreso then a chanters mez even, so always make sure you FD before your tank breaks mez. </P><P>During a raid... fuck heal everyone. No reason not to, i've never had a player bitch about me casting shadowbond on them. make a blank assist key and just randomly target mobs and mash on it to see who theyre beating on. You can see exactly who's pulling aggro when, which is awesome for popping a quick heal onto that chanter thats about to bite it from a resisted mez or whatever. IT costs TEN mana and you can save someones ass with it, all the while doing dmg to the mob with lifetaps and what not. </P><P></P><P>my xp group spell lineup is pretty constant, and works really well for me. </P><P>ST<BR>deflux<BR>ZToV<BR>Shadowbond<BR>whatever appropriate dot/nuke/slow/groupbuff here<BR>arch<BR>augmentation of death<BR>fd</P><P>i set a hotkey to just /assist in my fourth slot, which makes it super easy to thumb alt and press it again to zap a heal off. </P><P>i cant say this is the right way to play a necro...<BR>but at the very least it makes me feel useful. =D</P><P>hope this helps some of ya out</P><P> </font></td>
